# Pet Circle — Screen Completion Guide

## How to Use This File

This is a checklist of remaining gaps in the app UI. When working on a screen, consult the relevant section below. Completed items have been removed — only open work remains.

Stores are documented in the `state-management.mdc` rule file.
User story status is tracked in the `user-story-map.mdc` rule file.

---

## Priority 1 — Missing Features (no implementation)

These features have zero UI and need to be built from scratch.

| Feature | Impact | Suggested Location |
|---------|--------|--------------------|
| Edit pet profile | Can't update name, breed, photo | Edit mode on `pet_detail_screen.dart` or edit sheet |
| Delete / archive pet | Can't remove a pet | Swipe-to-delete or menu on `owner_dashboard.dart`; `petStore.removePet()` exists |
| User profile management | No way to edit name or photo | Profile section in settings or dedicated screen |
| Caregiver route | `CareCircleDashboard` unreachable | Add route to `app_routes.dart` and `main.dart`; add caregiver role option |

